# Docker Standard

## Purpose

Define containerization standards for the enterprise e-commerce platform.

Docker provides consistent environments across development, CI, and production.

---

## Container Strategy

| Environment | Usage |
|-------------|-------|
| Local development | docker compose for PostgreSQL, Redis, optional services |
| CI | Service containers + application test containers |
| Production | Container orchestration (Kubernetes, ECS, or managed platform) |

Application code runs natively in local dev (hot reload) with containerized dependencies — not always fully containerized during development.

---

## Project Structure

```
/
├── docker/
│   ├── Dockerfile.api
│   ├── Dockerfile.web
│   └── nginx.conf (if applicable)
├── docker-compose.yml
├── docker-compose.override.yml  # local overrides (gitignored patterns)
└── .dockerignore
```

---

## Dockerfile Standards

### Multi-Stage Builds

```dockerfile
# Dockerfile.api
FROM python:3.12-slim AS builder
WORKDIR /app
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir poetry
COPY pyproject.toml poetry.lock ./
RUN poetry export -f requirements.txt --output requirements.txt

FROM python:3.12-slim AS runtime
WORKDIR /app
RUN addgroup --system app && adduser --system --ingroup app app
COPY --from=builder /app/requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt
COPY apps/api/ .
USER app
EXPOSE 8000
HEALTHCHECK CMD curl -f http://localhost:8000/health || exit 1
CMD ["uvicorn", "src.main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]
```

### Rules

- Pin base image version (`python:3.12-slim`, not `python:latest`)
- Run as non-root user
- Multi-stage to minimize image size
- No secrets in Dockerfile or image layers
- `.dockerignore` excludes `.git`, `node_modules`, `__pycache__`, `.env`
- Include HEALTHCHECK instruction

### Web Dockerfile

```dockerfile
FROM node:20-alpine AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY apps/web/package*.json ./
RUN npm ci
COPY apps/web/ .
RUN npm run build

FROM node:20-alpine AS runtime
WORKDIR /app
RUN addgroup -S app && adduser -S app -G app
COPY --from=builder /app/.next/standalone ./
COPY --from=builder /app/.next/static ./.next/static
COPY --from=builder /app/public ./public
USER app
EXPOSE 3000
HEALTHCHECK CMD wget -qO- http://localhost:3000/api/health || exit 1
CMD ["node", "server.js"]
```

Use Next.js standalone output for minimal production image.

